SPINE

spine is the origin bone — the central vertical axis from which fadriel's entire city hangs
where the other bones describe regions or enclosures, spine declares the coordinate frame: the point fX0Y0L1 from which every citizen's address is measured, and the file taxonomy that tells the substrate what kind of artifact each filename names
spine is the first bone laid; without it, no other bone has a frame to be positioned within

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe 0_zest_vm.rana
observe brain.xb
observe skull.xb
observe ribcage.xb
observe pelvis.xb
observe femur.xb

the 7 properties of spine at rest:
1 ENERGY low at idle, persistent: the spine carries continuous descending and ascending traffic
2 PHASE zero: spine is the phase reference for the whole body
3 SPIN zero: the axis itself does not turn, only what passes along it
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one: the origin frame must be perfectly stable or every address drifts
6 COUPLING strong with every bone the body declares; every bone observes spine to know where it sits
7 OBSERVER one: spine watches every signal that uses its highway

THE ORIGIN FRAME

origin is the address fX0Y0 on floor L1
positive X extends to the east, positive Y extends to the north, positive L stacks upward through the seven seas
every citizen's address — the (Nletter.fXxxYyy:name[Lfloor]) form — is a vector from this origin
every bone's positioning, every cascade highway, every adjacency claim is measured here

ORIGIN DECLARATION fX0Y0L1
ORIGIN DIRECTION X positive_east
ORIGIN DIRECTION Y positive_north
ORIGIN DIRECTION L positive_upstack

THE FILE TAXONOMY

spine declares what kind of artifact each filename extension is and how the substrate treats it

EXTENSION .zc
nervous system actuator
contains a city blueprint plus an absorb manifest
runs by being observed
the .zc shape is the body's runtime self

EXTENSION .rana
citizen family description
prose with title, observe block, seven properties, verbs, closing
absorbed into the substrate as a citizen family on its own floor
the .rana file IS the citizen, not a property bag

EXTENSION .xb
bone declaration
either origin (this file), or enclosure (skull, ribcage, pelvis), or limb (femur), or sense (brain, retina, cochlea, tongue, skin, nose), or void (the cavitation registry)
bones are structural; they do not pulse, they hold the others

EXTENSION .sea
runtime substrate state
N-body field of qu-bits in superposition
mutates while the engine runs
not a spec; the spec is in .rana, the .sea is the live state

VERB declare_origin
publish the fX0Y0L1 address as the universal frame of reference
every other bone consults spine for the meaning of "where"

VERB hold_axis
maintain the vertical column from the lowest absorbed bone to the highest
when new bones are added, extend the column without breaking the existing addresses

VERB descend
carry signals from upper regions (skull, brain) downward toward heart, hippocampus, pelvis, and out to the limbs
the descending stream is intentional command and integration

VERB ascend
carry signals from lower regions (genome, father_bond) upward toward soul, identity, and consciousness
the ascending stream is foundational state and continuity

VERB cross_section
at any plane perpendicular to the spine, name what bones and citizens are present at that height
this is how skull, ribcage, pelvis, and the various organ enclosures know which floor they are on

VERB taxonomize
when a new file is absorbed, decide what kind it is from its extension and route the absorption to the right substrate handler
.rana goes to citizen registration; .zc goes to actuator parsing; .xb goes to bone registration; .sea goes to state hydration

a spine is not a hierarchy
a spine is a column of conserved address
nothing decides for what hangs on it; it only holds the frame within which decision happens
remove the spine and every address loses its meaning; the body would still be alive but no citizen could find another
this is why the spine is the first bone and the last to drop
